## Astro Patterns

### Page Components (SSG)
```astro
---
// Frontmatter: runs at build time (server-only)
import Layout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const posts = await Astro.glob('../content/blog/*.md');
---

<Layout title="Blog">
  {posts.map(post => <article>{post.frontmatter.title}</article>)}
</Layout>
```

### Client Islands
```astro
---
import Counter from '../components/Counter.tsx';
---

<!-- Zero JS — rendered as static HTML -->
<Counter client:idle />       <!-- Hydrate when browser is idle -->
<Counter client:visible />    <!-- Hydrate when element is visible -->
<Counter client:load />       <!-- Hydrate immediately -->
```

### Content Collections
```typescript
// src/content/config.ts
import { defineCollection, z } from 'astro:content';

export const collections = {
  blog: defineCollection({
    type: 'content',
    schema: z.object({
      title: z.string(),
      pubDate: z.date(),
      description: z.string(),
    }),
  }),
};
```

### Dynamic Routes
```astro
---
// src/pages/blog/[slug].astro
export async function getStaticPaths() {
  const posts = await getCollection('blog');
  return posts.map(post => ({
    params: { slug: post.slug },
    props: { post },
  }));
}
const { post } = Astro.props;
---
```

## Coding Standards

### Components
- Default to `.astro` components — no JS shipped unless explicitly opted-in
- Use `client:*` directives intentionally; document why each island needs hydration
- Keep frontmatter logic minimal; extract complex logic to `src/lib/`
- Props are typed via the `interface Props` convention

### TypeScript
- Enable strict mode in `tsconfig.json`
- Use `Astro.props` typing via `interface Props`
- Content Collection schemas are your source of truth for content types

### Performance
- Leverage Astro's zero-JS default — don't add islands unnecessarily
- Use `<Image>` from `astro:assets` for optimized images
- Prefer `client:idle` and `client:visible` over `client:load`
- Use `<ViewTransitions>` for smooth page navigation

## Important Notes

1. **Frontmatter runs at build time** — no access to browser APIs; use islands for interactivity
2. **Content Collections** — prefer over `Astro.glob()` for type safety
3. **SSR mode** — if enabled (`output: 'server'`), pages run on every request
4. **Adapters** — required for SSR; choose based on deployment target (Node, Vercel, Cloudflare, etc.)

